This was done for Ubuntu 18.04 LTS.

################ MINIMAL ####################
FIXES
1. Increment mouse speed (Settings)
2. Fix right click
  | Install gnome-tweaks with apt (3.28.1)
  | Change mouse emulation to Area
3. Write file /etc/X11/xorg.conf
   Section "Device"
     Identifier  "Intel Graphics"
     Driver      "intel"
     Option      "Backlight"  "intel_backlight"
   EndSection

APPS
1. Install Chrome (Used google-chrome 77.0.3865.90)
  | sudo nano /etc/apt/sources.list.d/google-chrome.list
    | deb [arch=amd64] http://dl.google.com/linux/chrome/deb/ stable main
  | wget https://dl.google.com/linux/linux_signing_key.pub
  | sudo apt-key add linux_signing_key.pub
  | sudo apt update
  | rm linux_signing_key.pub
  | sudo apt-get install google-chrome-stable
2. Okular with apt (okular 1.3.3)
3. Spotify with snap (spotify 1.1.10)
4. Install Emacs (26.3)
  * libx11-dev
  * libxpm-dev
  * libjpeg-dev
  * libpng-dev
  * libgif-dev
  * libtiff-dev
  * libgtk2.0-dev
  * libxpm-dev
  * automake
  * autoconf
  * gnutls-dev
  * mailutils
  | Go to Ecuador Mirror
  | ./configure
  | sudo make
  | sudo make install

I3 RELATED STUFF:
1. Install feh with apt (2.23.2)
2. Install xbacklight with apt (1.2.1)
3. Install scrot with apt (0.8)
4. Install betterlockscreen
  * libxcb-randr0-dev
  * libxcb-xrm
  * checkinstall
  * git clone https://github.com/PandorasFox/i3lock-color
  * git tag -f "git-$(git rev-parse --short HEAD)
  * autoreconf -i && ./configure && make
  * sudo checkinstall --pkgname=i3lock-color --pkgversion=1 -y
  * git clone https://github.com/pavanjadhaw/betterlockscreen
  * sudo cp betterlockscreen /usr/local/bin
5. Install i3blocks with apt (1.4.4).
6. Install compton with apt (0.1)

Packages:
1. Install Python (3.7.4)
  * sudo apt-get install
  * build-essential
  * zlib1g-dev
  * libffi-dev
  * libreadline-gplv2-dev
  * libncursesw5-dev
  * libssl-dev
  * libsqlite3-dev
  * tk-dev
  * libgdbm-dev
  * libc6-dev
  * libbz2-dev
  | Download .tar from python page.
  | tar -xvf Python-x.x.x.tar.xz
  | Change to directory extracted.
  | ./configure
  | sudo make
  | sudo make install
  | Add pip to path (See bashrc file)
  - numpy
  - simpy
  - matplotlib
  - sympy
2. Install texlive
  | sudo apt-get install texlive-full
3. Install ghcup
  * Install curl 7.58.0 with apt.
  * libgmp-dev
  * libncurses-dev
  | curl https://get-ghcup.haskell.org -sSf | sh
4. Install Agda (2.6.0.1)
  | cabal update
  | cabal install Agda
  | agda-mode setup
5. Install git with apt.
6. Install R (3.6.1)
  * gfortran
  * libcurl4-openssl-dev
  | Download tar ball from R webpage.
################### ADD ONS AND COSMETHIC ########################
COSMETHIC:
1. Theme
  | Install lxappeareance (0.6.3)
  | Select desired theme.
2. Load images at Pictures.

APPS:
1. VLC with snap (vlc 3.0.7)
2. Install Pycharm.
  | Download tar
  | Move folder to /opt/
  | Run {folder}/bin/pycharm.sh
  | Add to path
  | Create .desktop.
3. Install Popcorn Time.
  | sudo apt update && sudo apt install libcanberra-gtk-module libgconf-2-4
  | Install tar from active website.
  | Put it in /opt/
  | Add to path.
  | Create desktop.
4. Remmina (Remote Desktop) (1.2.0)
  | sudo apt-get install remmina remmina-plugin-*
5. Libreoffice
  | Installed with snap.
6. Install arandr.
  | Install with apt.

PACKAGES:
1. Install xrandr (7.7) :
  | sudo apt-get install x11-xserver-utils
2. Install wine (4.17)
  * flex with apt (2.6.4)
  * bison wuth apt (2.3.0)
  | Download tar from Wine.
  | ./configure --enable-win64
  | make
  | sudo make install